## =====================================================
## ORDER WORKFLOW
## =====================================================

```
                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
                    │                                     │
                    ▼                                     │
DRAFT → PENDING → CONFIRMED → PREPARING → READY → LOADING → SHIPPED → DELIVERED
                    │              │
                    │              ▼
                    │     SUBSTITUTION_PENDING ──┐
                    │              │             │
                    │              ▼             │
                    │     (Customer approves) ───┘
                    │
                    ▼
               CANCELLED

Payment Status (parallel track):
AWAITING_DEPOSIT → DEPOSIT_RECEIVED → AWAITING_BALANCE → FULLY_PAID
```

## =====================================================
## BUSINESS RULES
## =====================================================

### Order Modification Surcharges
| Days Before Loading | Surcharge |
|---------------------|-----------|
| > 30 days | $0 (free) |
| 15-30 days | $0 (warning shown) |
| 7-14 days | $50 or 2% of order |
| < 7 days | $100 or 5% of order |
| After loading | Modification blocked |

### Payment Terms (typical)
- 30% T/T deposit, 70% before shipment
- 100% T/T before shipment (new customers)
- Net 30/60/90 (established customers with credit)
- L/C at sight (large orders)

### Substitution Rules
- Substitution request expires after 72 hours (configurable)
- Auto-reject if no response = remove item from order
- Customer can request backorder instead of substitute
- Price difference: if substitute is cheaper, customer gets credit

## =====================================================
## IMPORTANT CODING RULES
## =====================================================

1. **Always use CSS variables** for colors: `var(--color-text-primary)`
2. **Multi-tenant**: Always filter by `companyId` in database queries
3. **Warehouse users NEVER see prices**: Check role before showing prices
4. **Soft deletes**: Set `isActive: false`, never DELETE
5. **Log all changes**: Create audit record for orders, payments, substitutions
6. **Complete files**: When editing, provide the COMPLETE file
7. **TypeScript strict**: Always type everything properly
8. **No external UI libraries**: Use custom components with Tailwind
9. **Notification abstraction**: Use NotificationService, never send directly

